<h3 class='title'>WYSIWIG</h3><div id='content'><p><p>I have downloaded and installed a WYSIWIG editor. That is a "What You See Is What You Get" editor. It allows all the bells and whistles of text formatting. Features include:</p><p></p><ol><li>Lists (ordered and un ordered)</li><li>images</li><li>text colours</li><li>text and image alignment</li><li><b>bold&nbsp;</b><i>italic&nbsp;</i><u>underlined</u>&nbsp;<strike>strikethrough</strike>&nbsp;<sub>subscript&nbsp;</sub>and&nbsp;<sup>superscript</sup>&nbsp;text formatting</li><li>Tables</li><li><code>Code blocks<br></code></li><li><p style="" class="">Quotes</p></li><li>Videos</li><li>links</li><li>and a few other things</li></ol><div>It's fairly easy to use and was fairly easy to install. I need to check it for security holes. I don't want users to be able to write scripts that will end up on the news page. This is probably the last thing I need to do to the post editor. Now I need to make them paginated so they aren't all just listed on one page.&nbsp;<span id="sceditor-end-marker" class="sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore" style="line-height: 0; display: none;"> </span><span id="sceditor-start-marker" class="sceditor-selection sceditor-ignore" style="line-height: 0; display: none;"> </span></div></p></div><div class='pull-right' id='date'>Tue 22nd Oct 2013 18:40</div>